WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:02.794
Oh, my God,
did you see the calves

00:02.794 --> 00:04.421
on the new Sparkletts guy?

00:04.421 --> 00:07.049
I snuck a picture and
I've already sent it to you.

00:07.049 --> 00:08.300
You are such
a good friend.

00:08.300 --> 00:09.343
I know.
Thank you.

00:09.343 --> 00:10.928
Okay, so,
how's the wedding?

00:10.928 --> 00:13.305
Oh, there is a poppy seed
on the groom's side.

00:13.305 --> 00:14.473
Yeah, it's right--
Some people say

00:14.473 --> 00:16.225
that we're too close,
but I-I don't get it.

00:16.225 --> 00:18.060
[ Sighs ] It's too deep. Alright.

00:18.060 --> 00:19.520
I will see you at lunch. Bye.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.313
[ Sighs ]

00:23.565 --> 00:25.192
[ Computer chimes ]

00:25.192 --> 00:26.485
Oh, no.

00:26.485 --> 00:28.779
Eww. Floss much?
[ Gasps ]

00:28.779 --> 00:31.615
Nell?
Nell Serrano?

00:31.615 --> 00:33.784
Piper Ashford. Mm.

00:33.784 --> 00:35.702
We were the same age.

00:35.702 --> 00:37.371
Yeah,
except you got old.

00:37.371 --> 00:38.830
And you died.
I know.

00:38.830 --> 00:39.998
Super sadsies.

00:39.998 --> 00:41.041
So is this where
you work?

00:41.041 --> 00:43.043
Is this, like,
a factory of some kind?

00:43.043 --> 00:45.754
It's a newsroom.

00:45.754 --> 00:48.340
News is kind of like TikTok,
but for people who can read.

00:48.340 --> 00:50.217
I love
your tiny little cubby.

00:50.217 --> 00:51.301
It's kind of like
the teachers' lounge

00:51.301 --> 00:52.594
that you used to
eat lunch in.

00:52.594 --> 00:54.805
Howdy, Ace.
[ Laughs ]

00:54.805 --> 00:56.640
I'm sorry.
I'm trying out new greetings.

00:56.640 --> 00:58.100
It's a work in progress.

00:58.100 --> 00:59.476
Of course you're friends
with this goober.

00:59.476 --> 01:00.978
Anyway, I was wondering
if you got my e-mail

01:00.978 --> 01:02.729
about the influencer.

01:02.729 --> 01:04.314
Actually, I went to high school
with her.
[ Gasps ]

01:04.314 --> 01:05.649
Do you happen to know
how she died?

01:05.649 --> 01:06.858
That's not important.

01:06.858 --> 01:08.485
It's super tragic.

01:08.485 --> 01:10.404
She was taking a selfie
and she fell off a cliff.

01:10.404 --> 01:11.488
Ha!

01:12.656 --> 01:15.242
Oh, that is so perfect.

01:15.242 --> 01:16.243
Yeah, it was.

01:16.243 --> 01:18.203
I managed to post it
on the way down.

01:18.203 --> 01:20.455
I'm worried this job
is making you callous, Nell.

01:20.455 --> 01:22.583
No, you don't understand.
Piper was a nightmare.

01:22.583 --> 01:25.502
She was cruel and shallow
and conceited and...

01:25.502 --> 01:26.837
seems like she still is.

01:26.837 --> 01:28.422
Since the two of you knew
each other, go ahead

01:28.422 --> 01:30.340
and take more time
with this if you need to.

01:30.340 --> 01:31.842
Oh. Oh, no.

01:31.842 --> 01:33.719
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

01:33.719 --> 01:35.846
I'll be done with this one
real soon.
Real soon.

01:35.846 --> 01:37.931
[ Clears throat ]

01:37.931 --> 01:39.600
Okay,
so, here we go.

01:39.600 --> 01:42.102
This is what we call
a "cursory obituary."

01:42.102 --> 01:44.187
It's, uh, superficial,
just like you.
Hmm?

01:44.187 --> 01:46.189
And it's just
a few brief sentences

01:46.189 --> 01:48.608
in the back of the paper
right next to the denture ads,

01:48.608 --> 01:51.236
because that is
all you deserve.
Rude!

01:51.236 --> 01:54.406
And I don't want to spend
any more time with you, so--

01:54.406 --> 01:55.574
Same, here, bit--
Boom!

01:55.574 --> 01:58.035
Ha ha. Ha ha.

01:58.035 --> 02:00.078
Oh, you have a little
poppy seed in your teeth.

02:00.078 --> 02:01.204
Oh. Yeah.

02:01.204 --> 02:02.664
May I?
No, Tina!

02:02.664 --> 02:04.541
What?
Ew. You cannot put
your fingers in my mouth.

02:04.541 --> 02:05.959
You can put your fingers
in <i>my</i> mouth.

02:05.959 --> 02:07.586
I don't want to put my fingers
in your mouth.

02:07.586 --> 02:08.670
Okay.

02:08.670 --> 02:13.508
♪

02:13.508 --> 02:16.511
- Captions by VITAC--

02:16.511 --> 02:19.681
Ugh, I hate when Ben
packs me chickpeas for lunch.

02:19.681 --> 02:20.932
- Sammy?
- Hmm?

02:20.932 --> 02:22.351
Trade you for your burger.
You're insane.

02:22.351 --> 02:24.645
And you haven't stolen
a single one of my fries,

02:24.645 --> 02:26.938
so what is going on?

02:26.938 --> 02:29.316
Ah, I'm just kind of having
a weird day, you know?

02:29.316 --> 02:31.318
I-I wrote this obituary
about a girl

02:31.318 --> 02:32.361
I went to high school with,

02:32.361 --> 02:34.237
and it's just got me...

02:34.237 --> 02:36.073
ugh, thinking about that time.

02:36.073 --> 02:37.783
I loved high school.

02:37.783 --> 02:39.368
As you can imagine, at a school
for the performing arts,

02:39.368 --> 02:40.786
I was kind of a big deal.

02:40.786 --> 02:42.537
Were you?
I even played
Racetrack Higgins

02:42.537 --> 02:44.331
in our school production
of "Newsies."

02:44.331 --> 02:47.000
Not only did that role ignite
my passion for journalism,

02:47.000 --> 02:49.711
but also, the local paper raved
that my performance was,

02:49.711 --> 02:52.089
and I quote, "competent."

02:52.089 --> 02:53.507
I mean, I also loved
high school,

02:53.507 --> 02:55.509
except for I wasn't
one of the popular kids,

02:55.509 --> 02:57.135
so I was kind of
just friends with everyone.

02:57.135 --> 02:58.845
That's what all
the popular girls say.

02:58.845 --> 03:00.555
I should know because
I say it all the time.

03:00.555 --> 03:01.932
What?!
Come on.

03:01.932 --> 03:03.684
Okay.

03:03.684 --> 03:05.977
I really just couldn't wait
till high school was over.

03:05.977 --> 03:07.187
Just felt like a waste of time.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.980
I'm really happy those days
are over.

03:08.980 --> 03:10.565
Are they, though?

03:10.565 --> 03:11.900
I feel like an office
is just a high school

03:11.900 --> 03:14.319
with more gossip
and fewer accidental erections.

03:14.319 --> 03:15.654
That kind of is true.

03:15.654 --> 03:17.322
We all sit
at our own desks,

03:17.322 --> 03:19.533
seeking approval
from other people,

03:19.533 --> 03:21.201
and then
you've got the cliques.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.911
The geeks, the jocks,

03:22.911 --> 03:26.039
the cool seniors,
teacher's pet,

03:26.039 --> 03:27.582
the weird loner,
and then there's always

03:27.582 --> 03:29.584
that one super-intense
Queen Bee.

03:29.584 --> 03:30.961
Nell?
Oh, God. Yeah?

03:30.961 --> 03:32.587
I'd like to see you
in my office,

03:32.587 --> 03:34.381
but please don't follow
for at least 30 seconds.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.883
I don't want people to think
we're walking together.

03:36.883 --> 03:38.802
One, two--

03:38.802 --> 03:39.719
You don't have to count, babe.
It's okay.
Yeah, no.

03:39.719 --> 03:40.720
Are you sure?
Yeah. It's fine.

03:40.720 --> 03:42.889
How would you like to write

03:42.889 --> 03:45.225
your first-ever
front-page obituary?

03:45.225 --> 03:46.810
Are you serious?

03:46.810 --> 03:47.936
Yes.

03:47.936 --> 03:49.604
I would.

03:49.604 --> 03:51.606
I promise not
to let you down, Lexi.

03:51.606 --> 03:54.484
Okay, great.
This is the assignment.

03:54.484 --> 03:56.361
Why? [ Clears throat ]
I don't understand.

03:56.361 --> 03:59.197
I-I turned in
this obit already.

03:59.197 --> 04:00.490
Oh, my God.
You're, like, obsessed with me.

04:00.490 --> 04:02.367
Yes, you did write it already,
but it was--

04:02.367 --> 04:03.702
oh, gosh, what's the term?--

04:03.702 --> 04:05.120
stanky garbage.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.788
I like her. Mm.

04:06.788 --> 04:10.375
What's the first thing you
notice about Piper's Instagram?

04:10.375 --> 04:12.085
She mangled the spelling
of "entrepreneur."

04:12.085 --> 04:13.920
She had
four million followers.

04:13.920 --> 04:15.714
Two million more than
Bryce Dallas Howard.

04:15.714 --> 04:17.299
No big deal.

04:17.299 --> 04:19.384
Followers that will be driven
to the newspaper

04:19.384 --> 04:22.137
if you write a warm
and thoughtful obituary.

04:22.137 --> 04:24.389
Mm-hmm.

04:24.389 --> 04:26.475
Oh.
Hmm?

04:26.475 --> 04:29.102
When I stop talking,
it means the meeting is over.

04:29.102 --> 04:31.062
See? Mm.

04:31.062 --> 04:32.230
Oh, that makes it
less personal.

04:32.230 --> 04:33.023
Still hurtful, though.

04:34.441 --> 04:36.526
Ha ha.
Ooh!

04:36.526 --> 04:37.569
[ Whistling ]

04:37.569 --> 04:39.446
- Oh!
- Aw.

04:42.866 --> 04:44.409
Take it, Dennis.
Three-pointer.

04:47.496 --> 04:48.997
Or you can just throw it
back to us.

04:48.997 --> 04:55.045
♪

04:55.045 --> 04:57.589
You okay?
Oh, no.

04:57.589 --> 05:00.050
Did Tina flip her eyelids
inside out again?

05:00.050 --> 05:02.511
Someone hung a basketball hoop
in the bullpen.

05:02.511 --> 05:03.887
Oh, that's cool.
No, not cool!

05:03.887 --> 05:06.389
I don't like basketball.

05:06.389 --> 05:09.184
Duh. You thought the Utah Jazz
was a Mormon swing band.

05:09.184 --> 05:11.102
Karl Malone
is a bass player's name.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.229
LeBron, think fast.
Whoo!

05:12.229 --> 05:13.355
Aah!
Ooh.

05:13.355 --> 05:15.524
[ Laughs ]

05:15.524 --> 05:16.942
That's very good.
Ah, thank you.

05:16.942 --> 05:18.443
We have fun.
We have fun here.

05:18.443 --> 05:19.861
Piper: You know
what you should write about?

05:19.861 --> 05:21.822
Huh?
My memorial.

05:21.822 --> 05:24.533
It's gonna be
the most fire funeral <i>ever.</i>

05:24.533 --> 05:26.326
The whole Piper Posse's
gonna be there--

05:26.326 --> 05:28.703
Kaitlyn, Mckenna,
Mckenzie, McKaitlyn.

05:28.703 --> 05:30.455
And you'll finally be able
to go to a cool party.

05:30.455 --> 05:31.748
I go
to a lot of cool parties.

05:31.748 --> 05:33.375
Escape rooms don't count.

05:33.375 --> 05:35.752
Hey, Cheugy, there's
some lady here to see you.

05:35.752 --> 05:38.630
Me, I tell my squad
not to visit me in the office

05:38.630 --> 05:41.633
because unlike you,
I have a dope work ethic.

05:41.633 --> 05:43.552
Mason out.

05:45.303 --> 05:46.304
Is that your mom?

05:46.304 --> 05:47.889
No, that's my friend.

05:47.889 --> 05:49.224
She looks like a mom.

05:49.224 --> 05:50.809
Yep. Still waving.

05:50.809 --> 05:53.311
You left your sweater
at the bar the other night. Mm.

05:53.311 --> 05:55.564
I was worried you might get
a little chilly.

05:55.564 --> 05:58.650
And I packed your
favorite snack, wine.

05:58.650 --> 06:00.569
Aww, thank you, Cricket.

06:00.569 --> 06:02.946
Today might be the day
I start drinking on the job.

06:02.946 --> 06:04.656
Are you okay?

06:04.656 --> 06:05.907
I got
the front page story,

06:05.907 --> 06:07.826
which is a huge step
in my career,

06:07.826 --> 06:09.286
but the woman
that I'm writing about

06:09.286 --> 06:10.787
was a mean girl
at my high school,

06:10.787 --> 06:12.998
and I'm just-- Ugh,
I'm just kind of starting

06:12.998 --> 06:14.624
to get her negative voice
in my head again.

06:14.624 --> 06:17.168
Do you know why mean girls
are so mean?
Hmm?

06:17.168 --> 06:20.171
Because deep down inside,
they are insecure.

06:20.171 --> 06:21.506
You think so?

06:21.506 --> 06:23.925
Jenny Witt tormented me
for two years

06:23.925 --> 06:26.052
because she was jealous
of me.

06:26.052 --> 06:27.804
On the other hand,
I did steal her boyfriend.

06:27.804 --> 06:29.180
Noice.

06:29.180 --> 06:30.807
Uh, thank you, Cricket.

06:30.807 --> 06:31.975
I should probably
get back to work.

06:31.975 --> 06:32.976
Okay.
Thank you, thank you.

06:32.976 --> 06:34.561
Bye.
Bye.

06:34.561 --> 06:36.271
[ Scoffs ] I can't believe
you're in charge

06:36.271 --> 06:38.815
of the last thing that's ever
gonna be written about me.

06:38.815 --> 06:40.859
I don't want an obituary
that sucks, okay?

06:40.859 --> 06:42.694
It won't suck.

06:42.694 --> 06:44.279
Although, writing about you
is like trying to put

06:44.279 --> 06:46.907
a positive spin
on the <i>Hindenburg.</i>

06:46.907 --> 06:50.410
Number one-- No one understands
your weird references.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.621
And, "B," if you don't
figure this out,

06:52.621 --> 06:54.331
you're totally
gonna boof this,

06:54.331 --> 06:55.790
just like you did
in the ninth grade.

06:55.790 --> 06:57.626
I don't know what
you're talking about.

06:57.626 --> 07:00.128
You don't remember your speech
from freshman year?

07:00.128 --> 07:02.922
As editor
of the <i>Bulldog Gazette,</i>

07:02.922 --> 07:05.842
I understand that
fiscal responsibility is--

07:05.842 --> 07:07.802
Pbht!
[ Laughter ]

07:07.802 --> 07:09.596
...is
a profoundly solemn oath...

07:09.596 --> 07:12.515
You suck, Nelly Fart-ado!
[ Laughs ]

07:12.515 --> 07:13.933
Go ahead, laugh.

07:13.933 --> 07:15.435
One day, I'm gonna be
running <i>The New York Times</i>

07:15.435 --> 07:16.978
and hanging out
with Josh Hartnett.

07:16.978 --> 07:19.898
[ Laughter ]

07:19.898 --> 07:21.941
Interesting.
I do not remember that.

07:21.941 --> 07:24.819
Yeah, you didn't exactly reach
your career goals, did you?

07:24.819 --> 07:27.113
And I don't think
that's Josh Hartnett.

07:29.658 --> 07:31.743
You know, I don't care
what you say.

07:31.743 --> 07:34.037
I'm a strong,
successful journalist.

07:34.037 --> 07:36.373
Maybe you fooled these dorks
into believing that,

07:36.373 --> 07:37.415
but I know the truth.

07:37.415 --> 07:39.084
You're still
insecure Nelly,

07:39.084 --> 07:40.752
and you know you're not gonna
be able to pull this off.

07:40.752 --> 07:41.878
Oh, my God.

07:41.878 --> 07:43.546
I need a break Oh.

07:43.546 --> 07:45.382
[ Gasps ]
Oh!

07:45.382 --> 07:46.758
[ Laughter ]

07:46.758 --> 07:49.094
Classic Fart-ado.

07:49.094 --> 07:50.136
[ Laughter continues ]

07:50.136 --> 07:51.429
Pbht!

07:51.429 --> 07:53.264
[ Laughter continues ]

07:55.934 --> 07:58.311
[ Sighs ] Hey.
Hmm?

07:58.311 --> 08:00.605
Could you read this obit
that I'm working on?

08:00.605 --> 08:02.148
Sure. It's not like I'm trying
to do anything important,

08:02.148 --> 08:03.817
like beat
Yusheng Du's world record!

08:03.817 --> 08:05.360
Great.

08:08.738 --> 08:09.364
[ Exhales deeply ]

08:11.116 --> 08:13.034
Piper Ashford died?
You knew her?

08:13.034 --> 08:14.411
I follow her.
Of course you did.

08:14.411 --> 08:16.413
She thinks deforestation's
super sadsies.

08:16.413 --> 08:18.081
I think Al Gore said
the same thing.

08:18.081 --> 08:19.332
Huh.
Huh.

08:19.332 --> 08:20.500
I'm sensing some sarcasm
there, huh?

08:20.500 --> 08:21.710
I grew up with Piper.

08:21.710 --> 08:24.087
She was a real butt-munch,
but now, luckily,

08:24.087 --> 08:26.631
I understand that she was,
uh, just jealous.

08:26.631 --> 08:29.801
"They're just jealous of you"
is an empty platitude

08:29.801 --> 08:32.429
that parents tell their kids
to make them feel better.

08:32.429 --> 08:34.389
I had
27 childhood bullies,

08:34.389 --> 08:36.474
and they were all
very well-adjusted.

08:36.474 --> 08:38.184
Neat. Great.
Can you please read this?

08:38.184 --> 08:39.310
It's for
the front page.

08:39.310 --> 08:41.688
[ Reading indistinctly ]

08:41.688 --> 08:42.981
[ Laughs ]
Hmm?

08:42.981 --> 08:44.232
It's great.
Really?

08:44.232 --> 08:45.358
It's cold and dry.

08:45.358 --> 08:46.443
It's like a list
of bullet points

08:46.443 --> 08:47.694
without any human emotion.

08:47.694 --> 08:48.737
I connect strongly to it.

08:48.737 --> 08:50.030
Awesome. Thanks.

08:52.949 --> 08:54.868
[ Knock on door ]

08:54.868 --> 08:56.369
Why is
your door closed?

08:56.369 --> 08:57.537
Oh, my God.
Are you hiding?

08:57.537 --> 08:58.955
<i>You're</i> hiding!

08:58.955 --> 09:00.749
Is this about
that basketball hoop?

09:00.749 --> 09:01.958
Sit.
What?

09:01.958 --> 09:05.628
Let me tell you a story
of a little boy...

09:05.628 --> 09:07.505
[ Gasps ]
...whose rugged good looks

09:07.505 --> 09:10.008
were often compared to that
of a young Denzel Washington.

09:10.008 --> 09:11.509
Ooh.
Yes.

09:11.509 --> 09:14.888
One day, said boy happened
upon some neighborhood youths

09:14.888 --> 09:17.766
who were playing a game
they called "street ball."

09:17.766 --> 09:19.392
They invited him to join.

09:19.392 --> 09:21.061
You know I-I know you're
talking about you, right?

09:21.061 --> 09:22.395
The boy was frightened. Oh.

09:22.395 --> 09:24.564
After all, he had never
thrown a ball before.

09:24.564 --> 09:25.857
Like, ever?

09:25.857 --> 09:27.067
There were no sports
at the Hirsch Academy

09:27.067 --> 09:28.735
for Performing Arts.

09:28.735 --> 09:31.571
But his acting teacher
often said,

09:31.571 --> 09:36.117
"New life experiences become
new acting experiences."

09:36.117 --> 09:37.660
So the boy
knew he had to try.

09:37.660 --> 09:39.829
I have a meeting that starts
at 2:00, so I should--

09:39.829 --> 09:41.539
The boy grasped the ball
in his hands,

09:41.539 --> 09:45.126
aimed it towards the hoop,
but when he threw it, somehow,

09:45.126 --> 09:46.461
against the very laws
of physics,

09:46.461 --> 09:48.797
it went straight up, came down,
smashed his glasses,

09:48.797 --> 09:50.548
broke his nose,
and at the sight of blood,

09:50.548 --> 09:52.342
the boy threw up
and fainted

09:52.342 --> 09:54.177
right there
on the basketball field.

09:54.177 --> 09:55.303
It's technically called
a court.

10:00.016 --> 10:02.102
This is about more
than just an office game.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.187
Eventually, I'm gonna have
a little kid, and they'll go,

10:04.187 --> 10:06.356
"Daddy, you wanna shoot
some hoops?"

10:06.356 --> 10:08.108
And I'll have to say,
"No, thank you.

10:08.108 --> 10:11.027
Daddy's
not very athletic."

10:11.027 --> 10:13.363
And then my kid
will laugh at me.

10:13.363 --> 10:16.324
And I will literally dissolve
into a puddle of shame.

10:16.324 --> 10:17.408
Oh, my God.
No, Dennis.

10:17.408 --> 10:18.827
I'm so sorry.

10:18.827 --> 10:20.578
I didn't realize how scary
this is for you.

10:20.578 --> 10:23.206
Hey. Hey!

10:23.206 --> 10:24.791
Why's the door closed?
Get in here.

10:24.791 --> 10:26.251
Oh. Ooh.

10:26.251 --> 10:28.336
Let me tell you the story
of a little boy

10:28.336 --> 10:29.587
who came upon
some neighborhood youths.

10:29.587 --> 10:31.756
Oh, okay, so this is
a very long story.

10:31.756 --> 10:33.133
It's okay.
I'll fill her in later. Okay.

10:33.133 --> 10:35.051
So, what is going on
with the obit?

10:35.051 --> 10:36.845
Oh, God,
I'm having writer's block.

10:36.845 --> 10:38.221
I mean, how am I supposed
to write something nice

10:38.221 --> 10:40.056
about a girl that used
to call me "Nelly Fart-ado"?

10:40.056 --> 10:41.766
[ Laughs ]
Ah.

10:41.766 --> 10:43.434
That's a good one.

10:43.434 --> 10:44.686
I mean, I used to actually
come up with nicknames

10:44.686 --> 10:46.104
for people
all the time in high school.

10:46.104 --> 10:47.522
Like, there was
this girl called Sarah.

10:47.522 --> 10:48.523
I called her Betty.

10:48.523 --> 10:50.316
How did you get Betty
from Sarah?

10:50.316 --> 10:52.861
She was always sweating
all the time,

10:52.861 --> 10:54.821
so we called her Sweaty Betty,
and then it just became Betty.

10:54.821 --> 10:56.614
That is extremely mean.

10:56.614 --> 10:58.867
What? No!
She loved it.

10:58.867 --> 11:01.035
She laughed
until she cried.

11:01.035 --> 11:02.328
[ Gasps ] Oh.
Hmm.

11:02.328 --> 11:03.454
Was I...
A bully?

11:03.454 --> 11:05.206
Like, a bad one.
Yes, definitely.

11:05.206 --> 11:07.709
I need to atone
for that sin.

11:07.709 --> 11:10.336
Too bad you can't go back
in time and not be a dick. Mm.

11:10.336 --> 11:13.840
But I could help you get
over your fear of basketball.

11:13.840 --> 11:15.508
I'd rather have cash.

11:15.508 --> 11:18.344
Then when I'm done with you,
nobody is gonna call you

11:18.344 --> 11:20.513
"Shaquille O'Squeal,"
"Larry Turd,"

11:20.513 --> 11:22.140
"Tragic Johnson"--
Mama, no.

11:22.140 --> 11:23.808
Do you hear yourself?
Can you please stop,
<i>por favor?</i>

11:23.808 --> 11:25.393
It's too much.

11:25.393 --> 11:26.978
[ P. A. beeps ]
Lexi on P. A.: <i>Nell Serrano,</i>

11:26.978 --> 11:29.105
<i>could you come see me
in the conference room?</i>

11:29.105 --> 11:31.191
<i>Nell Serrano
to the conference room.</i>

11:31.191 --> 11:32.901
When did she install
a P. A. system?

11:32.901 --> 11:34.611
[ P. A. beeps ]
<i>Last night.</i>

11:36.779 --> 11:38.448
Nell,
I wanted to check in

11:38.448 --> 11:40.867
on how the front-page
obituary is coming.

11:40.867 --> 11:43.203
It's, uh, going okay.

11:43.203 --> 11:44.704
Yeah.
A little slow, I guess.

11:44.704 --> 11:46.873
Ever since you started,
you have been begging me

11:46.873 --> 11:48.374
for a seat
at the dinner table. Mm...

11:48.374 --> 11:50.501
Now here I am with a chair
pulled out for you,

11:50.501 --> 11:52.837
and you are off pooping
in the guest house.

11:52.837 --> 11:54.839
- Mason!
- That's my name.

11:54.839 --> 11:56.549
Whatchu need,
baby girl?

11:56.549 --> 11:59.886
How would you like to write
a front-page obituary?

11:59.886 --> 12:01.262
Yes.

12:01.262 --> 12:02.889
Who's the subject?
Hold on. One second.

12:02.889 --> 12:05.225
Uh, you're giving him
the assignment?

12:05.225 --> 12:06.768
He's a freaking intern!

12:06.768 --> 12:08.603
I was the editor of the paper
at Dartmouth, you old crone.

12:08.603 --> 12:10.230
Silence!

12:10.230 --> 12:12.398
When I was a child,
every night,

12:12.398 --> 12:13.691
my father would
tell my brothers and me

12:13.691 --> 12:17.111
that he only had enough energy
for one good night hug.

12:17.111 --> 12:19.697
Whoever made the best case for
it would win his prized embrace.

12:19.697 --> 12:21.074
This explains so much.

12:21.074 --> 12:23.117
People work better
when they're in competition.

12:23.117 --> 12:25.203
Therefore, both of you
will write Piper's obituary,

12:25.203 --> 12:28.248
and whoever does a better job
will win the front page.

12:28.248 --> 12:31.751
Think of it as though you're
both competing for <i>my</i> hug.

12:31.751 --> 12:34.128
Although I will never
touch either of you.

12:34.128 --> 12:35.755
[ Sighs ]

12:35.755 --> 12:37.882
Cricket: She turned it
into a contest?

12:37.882 --> 12:39.592
And now Mason's going
to Piper's memorial,

12:39.592 --> 12:41.678
so I have to go, too.
[ Scoffs ]

12:41.678 --> 12:46.015
Ugh, and that stupid,
negative voice in my head... Mm.

12:46.015 --> 12:47.976
...is only gonna get louder.

12:47.976 --> 12:49.352
You know what's great
about getting older?

12:49.352 --> 12:51.104
Hmm?

12:51.104 --> 12:53.356
You have heard everything
that those voices have to say,

12:53.356 --> 12:55.608
and you just
stop listening.
[ Scoffs ]

12:55.608 --> 12:57.777
You know, my mom said that
you shouldn't allow yourself

12:57.777 --> 12:59.696
to become a pessimist.
Piper: Oh, my God.

12:59.696 --> 13:01.781
How could I have had faith
in you?
There are
some beautiful things...

13:01.781 --> 13:03.783
I thought you would
pull this off.

13:03.783 --> 13:06.160
You're a grown woman and you're
taking advice from this lady?

13:06.160 --> 13:08.288
...negativity
is the enemy of creativity.

13:08.288 --> 13:09.998
Why don't you tell
your mom friend

13:09.998 --> 13:13.751
that this negative voice inside
your head is actually a ghost?

13:13.751 --> 13:15.670
I'm sure she won't think
you're psycho at all.

13:15.670 --> 13:18.172
Because deep down, you know
that you're a sad little loser

13:18.172 --> 13:20.216
and now you can't even
write one single obituary.

13:20.216 --> 13:22.343
But you are a beautiful,
kind, lovely person.

13:22.343 --> 13:24.846
Face it, Nelly.
You peaked in high school.

13:24.846 --> 13:27.098
Would you just stop?!

13:27.098 --> 13:28.433
I'm sorry.
I was just--

13:28.433 --> 13:30.893
I was
just trying to help you.

13:30.893 --> 13:32.020
Sorry.

13:32.020 --> 13:34.522
No, I-I didn't--
I--

13:34.522 --> 13:36.941
[ Sighs ] It's, uh--
It's not you. I...

13:36.941 --> 13:39.360
I'll-- I'll see you later, okay?

13:39.360 --> 13:41.112
♪

13:45.116 --> 13:47.577
♪ It's about damn time ♪
Look at all the sponsors.

13:47.577 --> 13:50.079
Aw, my very last
Instagram post.

13:50.079 --> 13:51.664
[ Clicks tongue ]

13:51.664 --> 13:55.168
Oh, there's the photo ops,
and there's the omelet bar.

13:55.168 --> 13:56.961
You know, I curated
all of this in my will.

13:56.961 --> 13:58.671
Yeah, you mentioned that,
like, seven times.

13:58.671 --> 14:01.632
I better see if they set up
the refection yurt.

14:01.632 --> 14:04.135
Well, well, well.

14:04.135 --> 14:05.803
Look what
the cat threw up.

14:05.803 --> 14:07.472
Why are you dressed
like Tony Soprano?

14:07.472 --> 14:08.973
Oh, don't be a hater
'cause you're jelly.

14:08.973 --> 14:10.391
The front page is mine,

14:10.391 --> 14:12.351
so you might as well go home, Grandma.

14:12.351 --> 14:13.811
Ooh, churros!

14:13.811 --> 14:15.063
♪ Mm ♪

14:15.063 --> 14:16.731
♪ That's how I feel right now ♪

14:16.731 --> 14:19.150
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

14:19.150 --> 14:20.902
Cricket:
Hey, is this seat taken?

14:20.902 --> 14:22.653
[ Chuckles ]

14:22.653 --> 14:24.864
♪ I'm way too fine
to be this stressed, yeah ♪

14:24.864 --> 14:27.700
Oh.
Oh.

14:27.700 --> 14:30.870
I knew this was the last place
you wanted to be today.

14:30.870 --> 14:34.499
So I decided to come give you
some emotional support.

14:34.499 --> 14:37.043
Thank you, Cricket.

14:37.043 --> 14:38.377
My career might be ending,

14:38.377 --> 14:39.504
but at least I got
my friend with me.

14:39.504 --> 14:41.422
Yes, you do.

14:41.422 --> 14:42.715
♪ It's about damn time ♪

14:42.715 --> 14:45.760
Okay. Alright.
She is on there.

14:45.760 --> 14:48.096
Now tell me--
What is the ultimate goal?

14:48.096 --> 14:49.972
To play Jean Valjean
on Broadway.

14:49.972 --> 14:52.683
And to conquer your fear
and make a basket.
Yeah, mm-hmm.

14:52.683 --> 14:54.268
I was gonna say that,
but the first thing--

14:54.268 --> 14:55.978
Aah!
[ Glass shatters ]

14:55.978 --> 14:57.897
Alright.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.315
Now, you listen to me.

14:59.315 --> 15:01.359
When I'm done with you,
this entire newsroom

15:01.359 --> 15:04.570
is gonna see
you drain one from downtown.

15:04.570 --> 15:06.030
[ Frank Stallone's
"Far from Over" plays ]

15:06.030 --> 15:08.116
[ <i>Man speaking indistinctly</i> ]
I really like their costumes.

15:08.116 --> 15:09.200
Focus!

15:09.200 --> 15:10.618
In.
Let's go!

15:10.618 --> 15:13.037
Like a fish.
Let's go.

15:13.037 --> 15:14.122
What the [bleep]
was that?

15:14.122 --> 15:16.374
Now take the shot,
take the shot!

15:16.374 --> 15:17.917
Close. Mm-hmm.
And set.

15:17.917 --> 15:18.709
Okay.
♪ This is the end ♪

15:18.709 --> 15:20.044
Oh!
Oh.

15:20.044 --> 15:21.420
Very close.

15:21.420 --> 15:22.713
Okay.
We don't need to dribble.

15:22.713 --> 15:24.257
You want to put your hands
in the same position

15:24.257 --> 15:26.217
as Mariah Carey
doing a vocal run.

15:26.217 --> 15:27.385
<i>That</i> I understand.

15:27.385 --> 15:28.469
Okay.
Okay.

15:28.469 --> 15:30.221
[ Vocalizing ]

15:30.221 --> 15:33.558
♪ I need it all
'cause I am running over ♪

15:33.558 --> 15:37.562
♪

15:37.562 --> 15:39.730
[ Sighs ]

15:39.730 --> 15:42.191
I mean, we could just burn
the entire building down.

15:42.191 --> 15:44.485
[ Dance music plays ]

15:44.485 --> 15:49.240
Ah. Of course this is the most
perfect funeral in history.

15:49.240 --> 15:51.033
Oh.

15:51.033 --> 15:53.536
I'm not so sure sponsorship
is what makes a good funeral.

15:53.536 --> 15:54.912
What the heck
does she know?

15:54.912 --> 15:56.414
She's probably
still on Facebook.

15:56.414 --> 15:58.249
[ Laughs ]
If the Piper Posse were here,

15:58.249 --> 16:00.126
they would have loved
that sick burn.

16:00.126 --> 16:01.460
Where are they?

16:01.460 --> 16:04.297
If you ask me,
it's-- it's kind of sad.

16:04.297 --> 16:07.508
And not the way memorials
are supposed to be sad.

16:07.508 --> 16:08.593
Check that out.

16:08.593 --> 16:11.012
When Monty died,
everyone wanted

16:11.012 --> 16:12.346
to make
a speech about him.

16:12.346 --> 16:15.183
Hm.
I mean, it went on for hours.

16:15.183 --> 16:18.019
Piper may have had
four million followers,

16:18.019 --> 16:20.188
but I'm guessing she didn't
have a lot of friends.

16:20.188 --> 16:22.190
[ Scoffs ]
I have friends.

16:22.190 --> 16:23.316
I have tons of friends.

16:23.316 --> 16:25.401
They're probably
just parking.

16:25.401 --> 16:27.111
You know what?
Maybe you're right.

16:27.111 --> 16:30.448
I mean, I-I don't think she had
any real friends.

16:30.448 --> 16:31.908
Not even the Piper Posse.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.492
Are you high?

16:33.492 --> 16:35.119
I rushed Delta Gamma
with McCauley and McKendra.

16:35.119 --> 16:36.454
Yeah, she ruled
over those girls,

16:36.454 --> 16:38.122
but it was only
for their approval.

16:38.122 --> 16:39.540
Not because
they were friends.

16:39.540 --> 16:43.878
Even before social media,
Piper only had... followers.

16:43.878 --> 16:45.254
[ Scoffs ]

16:45.254 --> 16:46.547
Oh.

16:46.547 --> 16:48.841
I can't believe I actually
feel sorry for her.

16:48.841 --> 16:50.259
[ Scoffs ] Please.

16:50.259 --> 16:53.721
♪

16:53.721 --> 16:55.890
Huh.
I'll be back.

16:55.890 --> 16:57.058
Alright.
What are you doing?

16:57.058 --> 16:58.309
Where are you going?

16:58.309 --> 16:59.560
Hello?

16:59.560 --> 17:00.937
Excuse me, e--
[ Feedback whining ]

17:00.937 --> 17:01.812
Excuse me, everyone.

17:01.812 --> 17:03.397
Hey. Hi.

17:03.397 --> 17:05.274
Uh, I'm, uh, Nell Serrano.

17:05.274 --> 17:07.693
I went to high school
with Piper,

17:07.693 --> 17:10.071
and it is a little odd
that I'm the one up here

17:10.071 --> 17:11.322
because she was my bully.

17:11.322 --> 17:12.490
Piper:
No, I was not!

17:12.490 --> 17:14.909
You shut your ugly face,
Fart-ado!

17:14.909 --> 17:17.787
Uh, when I was young,

17:17.787 --> 17:22.375
Piper seemed confident
and popular,

17:22.375 --> 17:24.460
but now I can see
another side to her,

17:24.460 --> 17:28.965
a side that was probably
just as insecure as I was.

17:28.965 --> 17:33.553
As much as we try to curate
the way people see us...

17:33.553 --> 17:36.639
no one knows what's
really going on inside.

17:36.639 --> 17:39.934
You know, we can't be reduced
to a hashtag or a selfie,

17:39.934 --> 17:44.105
because we're all
so complicated.

17:44.105 --> 17:46.983
Some of us spend our lives
running from our fears

17:46.983 --> 17:50.027
before gathering the courage
to face them.

17:50.027 --> 17:53.406
Some of us are still trying
to fit in with the cool kids.

17:53.406 --> 17:57.618
And some of us are trying to
atone for the kid we used to be.

17:57.618 --> 18:00.329
All those flattering filters
on social media made

18:00.329 --> 18:03.207
Piper seem like
a perfect goddess,

18:03.207 --> 18:06.586
but, uh, she had--

18:06.586 --> 18:09.630
She had a negative voice
in her head, too.

18:09.630 --> 18:12.300
The funny thing about that mean
and internal voice

18:12.300 --> 18:13.884
is that it only hurts

18:13.884 --> 18:17.346
when we start
to believe it for ourselves.

18:17.346 --> 18:21.100
That's why we need a kind
and loving voice

18:21.100 --> 18:24.353
that can tell that cruel voice
to shut the hell up.

18:28.232 --> 18:30.401
I really think
that Piper deserved

18:30.401 --> 18:32.653
to have a kind voice in her life

18:32.653 --> 18:35.364
that told her
that she was good enough,

18:35.364 --> 18:37.700
even without
all these sponsors.

18:37.700 --> 18:41.996
So, wherever she is,
I hope she has that voice now.

18:41.996 --> 18:46.167
♪

18:46.167 --> 18:48.085
#PiperGotHerWings.

18:48.085 --> 18:50.171
Cricket: Yes!
Whoo! Whoo!

18:50.171 --> 18:51.756
[ Cheers and applause ]
Woman: Yes!

18:51.756 --> 18:56.927
♪

18:56.927 --> 18:58.012
Woman #2: Yes!

19:01.349 --> 19:04.185
You don't have to do this,
you know.

19:04.185 --> 19:06.520
No, this is gonna keep
happening to me.

19:06.520 --> 19:08.356
I have
to slay my dragons.

19:08.356 --> 19:10.066
Okay.

19:10.066 --> 19:12.193
But I just want you to know
whether you make it or not

19:12.193 --> 19:16.364
is not gonna make you a better
friend or father or person,

19:16.364 --> 19:20.159
because you are perfect
exactly how you are.

19:20.159 --> 19:22.620
Wow.

19:22.620 --> 19:24.830
You've come a long way
from the accidental bully

19:24.830 --> 19:25.998
you were in high school.
Thank you.

19:25.998 --> 19:27.500
Yes. You're welcome.

19:27.500 --> 19:28.751
[ Chuckles ]
And you know what?

19:28.751 --> 19:30.711
You're right.
I don't need this.

19:30.711 --> 19:31.754
Let's go get donuts.

19:31.754 --> 19:33.005
Yes! Can do that?
Yes.

19:33.005 --> 19:34.465
Please. Okay.
Come on. Bah.

19:36.717 --> 19:38.844
You made it!
You made it!
[ Laughs ] I made it!

19:38.844 --> 19:39.929
Oh, my God!

19:39.929 --> 19:42.056
Suck it, LeBrum Germs!

19:42.056 --> 19:43.099
Whoever you are.

19:43.099 --> 19:44.016
Whoever that is.

19:49.814 --> 19:53.359
Well, Mason, good news.

19:53.359 --> 19:55.528
You have officially joined
the ranks

19:55.528 --> 19:57.822
of everyone who
has ever disappointed me.

19:57.822 --> 19:59.699
Nell,
you get the front page.

20:01.283 --> 20:03.828
Your pathetic little victory
means nothing

20:03.828 --> 20:05.371
because my best days
are ahead of me

20:05.371 --> 20:06.747
and you've already peak--
Peaked?

20:06.747 --> 20:09.375
Yeah.
I've heard that one before.

20:09.375 --> 20:12.211
It doesn't
really bother me anymore.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.963
Well, that's no fun.

20:13.963 --> 20:16.090
Mm.

20:16.090 --> 20:18.092
What a dingus.

20:18.092 --> 20:20.553
You know he took five swag bags
from my memorial?

20:20.553 --> 20:22.388
[ Chuckles ]

20:22.388 --> 20:24.181
By the way, I should
probably tell you

20:24.181 --> 20:26.851
that what you said
about me was...

20:26.851 --> 20:28.436
nice.
Thank you.

20:30.896 --> 20:33.858
So, uh,
I guess this is goodbye.

20:33.858 --> 20:36.402
I just have one more thing
to tell you.

20:36.402 --> 20:37.570
Oh?

20:37.570 --> 20:40.197
You really put the "bitch"
in "obituary."

20:42.241 --> 20:45.411
Smell ya later, Fart-ado.

20:45.411 --> 20:47.079
Smell ya later, Piper.

20:52.501 --> 20:55.045
Mm-mm-mm.
Look at you.

20:55.045 --> 20:58.132
You got your obituary
on the front page.

20:58.132 --> 21:00.009
Girl, I'm proud.

21:00.009 --> 21:01.594
No, it really
is well done.

21:01.594 --> 21:03.387
I'm not crazy about
the headline, though.

21:03.387 --> 21:06.724
"Dope Influencer
Piper Ashford Totes Dead."

21:06.724 --> 21:08.434
That was, um, Lexi, uh,

21:08.434 --> 21:10.186
saying she wanted to be
"down with the kids."

21:10.186 --> 21:12.146
Wait, her name
was Piper Ashford?
Cricket: Mm. Mm.

21:12.146 --> 21:14.023
Please tell me you called her
"Pooper Ass-Turd."

21:14.023 --> 21:15.941
Where were you
20 years ago?

21:15.941 --> 21:17.234
I wasn't born. Okay.

21:17.234 --> 21:18.277
Thank you.
Oh!

21:18.277 --> 21:19.779
Okay. Thanks.
Okay?

21:19.779 --> 21:21.155
[ Laughter ]
